{"EXPUGN":[{"def":"To take by assault; to storm; to overcome; to vanquish; as, to expugn cities; to expugn a person by arguments.","pos":""}],"EXPUGNABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being expugnded.","pos":""}],"EXPUGNATION":[{"def":"The act of taking by assault; conquest.","pos":""}],"EXPUGNER":[{"def":"One who expugns.","pos":""}],"EXPULSE":[{"def":"To drive out; to expel.","pos":""}],"EXPULSION":[{"def":"The act of expelling; a driving or forcing out; summary removal from membership, association, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"The state of being expelled or driven out.","pos":""}],"EXPULSIVE":[{"def":"Having the power of driving out or away; serving to expel.","pos":""}],"EXPUNCTION":[{"def":"The act of expunging or erasing; the condition of being expunged.","pos":""}],"EXPUNGE":[{"def":"To blot out, as with pen; to rub out; to efface designedly; to obliterate; to strike out wholly; as, to expunge words, lines, or sentences.","pos":""},{"def":"To strike out; to wipe out or destroy; to annihilate; as, to expugne an offense.","pos":""}],"EXPURGATE":[{"def":"To purify; to clear from anything noxious, offensive, or erroneous; to cleanse; to purge; as, to expurgate a book.","pos":""}],"EXPURGATION":[{"def":"The act of expurgating, purging, or cleansing; purification from anything noxious, offensive, sinful, or erroneous.","pos":""}],"EXPURGATOR":[{"def":"One who expurgates or purifies.","pos":""}],"EXPURGATORIAL":[{"def":"Tending or serving to expurgate; expurgatory.","pos":""}],"EXPURGATORIOUS":[{"def":"Ex*pur`ga*to\"ri*ous, a.","pos":""}],"EXPURGATORY":[{"def":"Serving to purify from anything noxious or erroneous; cleansing; purifying.","pos":""}]}